Former Liverpool player, Mark Lawrenson, has predicted the English Premier League (EPL) matches to take place this weekend. Tottenham Hotspur will host Arsenal on Sunday evening, while Manchester United will face Manchester City at Old Trafford on Saturday afternoon. Chelsea will clash with Crystal Palace on Sunday at Stamford Bridge. Providing his predictions, Lawrenson was quoted by Paddy Power as saying: Aston Villa 1-2 Leeds United
Manchester United 0-2 Manchester City
Wolverhampton Wanderers 1-2 West Ham United
Nottingham Forest 2-1 Leicester City
Brighton 2-0 Liverpool
Everton 1-1 Southampton
Bournemouth 0-2 Brentford
Chelsea 2-1 Crystal Palace
Newcastle United 2-0 Fulham
Tottenham Hotspur 1-1 Arsenal